</title>
<subSubSection id="B6105AE7FBE8BD5018C4017BC9F5C44B" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" type="description">
<paragraph id="5CD5AAAD63D951DAD78A69D4CEDFCDDA" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="27D3E0746A14A517CBF9C53FBD6F83B6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Inula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9E626AC4CAFDF6840E0B19F797D7FDF7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Inula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. 522) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="5BB59A294C180347E0B7A011FDB13478" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicName id="73F3631816DD84D9E31DF0ABFF7C640A" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pappus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pappus</taxonomicName>
2reihig; die 
<normalizedToken id="5E0953CBC5EFEA49C63E816491827E30" originalValue="äußere" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">aeussere</normalizedToken>
Reihe einen 
<normalizedToken id="71A08A409B185A1AE337985BC23E5E7D" originalValue="gezähnten" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">gezaehnten</normalizedToken>
, kleinen Ring bildend, die innere Reihe aus 5
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="CBDE18B7E9D116DFC5696B3281AA10F2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">20 rauhen Borsten bestehend.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58E9F155BF57B50F1AF529ED57FBCCD5" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="D33B23D236702CC285724C90E3BF67EB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pulicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C554F242B27AB64573D598D45859EE19" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Pulicaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="FD53047472578CBE85E3FB727F4FB9C2" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 
<emphasis id="6D78CB74895C264CF8A77EBCEFF6E179" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">45 Arten</emphasis>
und ist in der 
<emphasis id="27A9F92151552D5542C65E914A590FC9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Alten Welt</emphasis>
, vor allem im 
<emphasis id="FD75C9EED62F8AFC56B177E54372E23D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Mittelmeergebiet</emphasis>
verbreitet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5129C13791001EE3F800186D3A1CBCE5" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<table id="CFF262C6056054BB3086811BDD4297F5" frame="void" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" rules="none" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
<tbody id="20356675794CA44638E34481253CAD48" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<tr id="0A7BDCFE0D1D2CC917970853836113EB" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<td id="46A9BF6CEE320912D0F6178CB43647E2" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" valign="top">
1. Pflanze 1 
<normalizedToken id="E2626CC63C67AD92416DA0F111CC54DE" originalValue="jährig" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">jaehrig</normalizedToken>
; obere 
<normalizedToken id="28CCABD27F719E39A2F174089D2BDA9C" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
mit abgerundetem Grund sitzend; 
<normalizedToken id="0F0CE12236BA0DFD4DA38CA936DD6A00" originalValue="Blütenköpfe" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Bluetenkoepfe</normalizedToken>
im Durchmesser ca. 1 cm, mit aufrechten, ca. 0,5 mm breiten 
<normalizedToken id="6C3D4BB8235D864A7AE6C3C3A801CA58" originalValue="Zungenblüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Zungenblueten</normalizedToken>
, die wenig 
<normalizedToken id="AEB544F4694988C8B1888A0C2E708E32" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">laenger</normalizedToken>
sind als die 
<normalizedToken id="53CFB2A689C63A2508A8A79B37D6FFB7" originalValue="Hülle" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Huelle</normalizedToken>
</td>
<td id="22A5146686CB88E09E8499B8D8DFD48C" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="0D59D79933F1EF3977604E5B56C24996" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<italic id="A7E1E7BDD6E5E3C4781FAB23CAD63F25" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">P. vulgaris</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1)
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="567EC2E7BEAA4848575483C180F8AE64" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<td id="B144B48E661AAAE42ECC621B32F4591F" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" valign="top">
1*. Pflanze ausdauernd, mit 
<normalizedToken id="1D643B070B5EF9A8CEEDC8A9AC30E528" originalValue="Ausläufern" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Auslaeufern</normalizedToken>
; obere 
<normalizedToken id="48160657635D5D0F145F65D6B249ACF8" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
den Stengel mit breit 
<normalizedToken id="0261713935584A1447E00554486E6F56" originalValue="herzförmigem" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">herzfoermigem</normalizedToken>
Grunde umfassend; 
<normalizedToken id="F813CF7C383080D7FF37EAB9849DB01D" originalValue="Blütenköpfe" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Bluetenkoepfe</normalizedToken>
im Durchmesser 1,5-3 cm, mit ca. 1 mm breiten, ausgebreiteten 
<normalizedToken id="DFA26F19800898F20D9DA6DB37140C68" originalValue="Zungenblüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Zungenblueten</normalizedToken>
</td>
<td id="0BE3B3A82852F108D12467B39595FCC6" align="left" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" valign="bottom">
<taxonomicName id="BBB5460FAB60532991E338C3F5528037" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pulicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dysenterica">
<italic id="1F0FEC9286116414B6F5A8475FA5F311" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">P. dysenterica</italic>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2)
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</paragraph>
